    "Strongly lensed images can form at lower magnification, where microlensing Scatter is lower for the lensed SN image that is far from the Einstein radius (with lower convergence/shear), but there is a limit since a convergence below 0.25 produces only single images (i.e., no strong lensing) and convergence below ∼0.35 produces a faint counterimage (close to lens center) that makes time-delay measurements more challenging.",
